[SN]TITLE[SN]
Paraglider rescued after injury on County Armagh mountain

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A paraglider has been rescued after being injured on a mountain in County Armagh.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The casualty, who was with a group of paragliders, was airlifted off Slieve Gullion at about 15:00 GMT on Sunday.
Mourne Mountain Rescue Team said the man had a "serious leg injury" and was taken to the Royal Victoria Hospital in Belfast.
The team had been training in the Annalong Valley when the emergency call came at 13:43 GMT.
Mourne Mountain Rescue Team, Belfast Coastguard, Irish coastguard, PSNI and the Northern Ireland Ambulance Service were all involved in the rescue.
"A total of 22 members responded and the team stood down at 18:17 GMT," Mourne Mountain Rescue said.
